# Lab-Grown Princess Cut Diamond: The Lab Princess Discount

The [princess cut](/princess-cut-diamond) is already the most affordable natural diamond shape — square geometry, maximum rough diamond yield, lower manufacturing cost than round. When you move to lab-grown, those starting advantages multiply into something dramatic. The cost reduction is not incremental. It restructures the entire grade hierarchy you would apply to a natural stone.

With a natural princess, you choose G-VS2 to balance beauty and budget. With a lab princess, D-IF — the absolute top of the color and clarity scale — costs less than a comparable natural G-VS2 by the time you reach 1.5 carats. The grade ceiling disappears at lab prices. This changes which questions you should even be asking.

The **Lab Princess Discount** is the compounding effect of lab pricing on princess cut diamonds specifically: lower base cost than round, lower base cost than most fancy shapes, and a price-per-carat that drops dramatically at the 1.5ct, 2ct, 3ct, and 4ct thresholds. Understanding how the discount compounds — and which certification extracts the most value — is what this guide covers.

## TL;DR — Lab-Grown Princess Cut Diamond {{year}}

- **Named concept:** The Lab Princess Discount — princess cut was already the cheapest natural shape. Lab manufacturing reduces that further. A [lab 1.51ct D-IF IGI princess at $3,006](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27428901?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) gives top color and flawless clarity for $794 more than a natural 1ct G-VS2 at $2,212.
- **Entry lab price:** G-VS2 lab 1ct princess starts under $600 at Blue Nile. Natural equivalent: $2,212. Savings: ~73%.
- **Top grade lab:** D-IF IGI 1.51ct at $3,006. D-IF IGI 1.52ct at $3,025. Natural D-IF 1ct would exceed $12,000.
- **GCAL value play:** [GCAL 1.76ct E-IF at $2,980](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29417594?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — more carat, top clarity, less money than IGI 1.51ct D-IF. GCAL certification is fully legitimate and priced below IGI/GIA.
- **Near-2ct:** [GCAL 1.96ct D-IF at $3,609](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28425374?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and [GCAL 1.99ct D-IF at $3,661](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29126772?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural 2ct G-VS2: $12,229. Saving: ~70%.
- **3ct:** [GCAL 3ct D-IF at $7,574](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29354742?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs IGI 3ct D-IF/FL at $9,577 — same diamond, $2,000 difference by certification alone.
- **5ct split:** IGI 5ct D-FL: ~$29,000. GIA 5ct D-FL: ~$55,000. Same diamond, GIA commands a ~90% premium for lab certification.
- **Resale:** Lab princess diamonds have dropped 80–90% in value since 2020 and continue falling. Buy lab only when resale is not a requirement.

